main event: On November 25, 1957, in Frankfort, Kentucky, a civilian reported seeing a round white object the size of a dime flying in a straight path for six seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as round, white, and the size of a dime.
The sighting lasted only six seconds, indicating a brief observation.
The conclusion suggested that the object was likely a balloon or possibly a meteor due to the short duration of the sighting.
The source of the report was a civilian from the Air National Guard (ANG).
The report mentioned that there were no photographs of the object.
result: prosaic explanation: possibly a balloon or meteor
witnesses: civilian from the Air National Guard (ANG)
